Name: BUBBLE
Explain:
A spray of bubbles
hits the foe. It
may lower the
foe¡¯s SPEED stat.

Name: EMBER
Explain: The foe is attacked with small flames. The foe may suffer a burn.

Name: GROWL
Explain:
The user growls in
a cute way, making
the foe lower its
ATTACK stat.

Name: GUST
Explain: Strikes the foe with a gust of wind whipped up by wings.

Name: LEECH SEED
Explain: A seed is planted on the foe to steal some HP for the user on every turn.

Name: QUICK ATTACK
Explain: An almost invisibly fast attack that is certain to strike first.

Name: SAND ATTACK
Explain: A lot of sand is hurled in the foe¡¯s face, reducing its accuracy.

Name: SCRATCH
Explain: Hard, pointed, and\nsharp claws rake\nthe foe.

Name: TACKLE
Explain:
A physical attack
in which the user
charges, full body,
into the foe.

Name: TAIL WHIP
Explain:
The user wags its
tail cutely, making
the foe lower its
DEFENSE stat.

Name: STRING SHOT
Explain:
The foe is bound
with strings shot
from the mouth to
reduce its SPEED.

Name: POISON STRING
Explain:
The foe is stabbed
with a toxic
barb, etc. It
may poison the foe.

Name: PECK
Explain: The foe is jabbed\nwith a sharply\npointed beak or horn.

Name: LEER
Explain:
The foe is given
an intimidating look
that lowers its
DEFENSE stat.

Name: LOW KICK
Explain:
A low, tripping kick
that inflicts more
damage on heavier
foes.

Name: Defense Curl
Explain: The user curls up to conceal weak spots and raise its DEFENSE stat.

Name: Bind
Explain: A long body or tentacles are used to bind the foe for two to five turns.

Name: Rock Throw
Explain: The foe is attacked with a shower of small, easily thrown rocks.

Name: Harden
Explain: The user stiffens all the muscles in its body to raise its DEFENSE stat.
